<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-06-20T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-06-20T14:00:00-05:00" n="285" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d285">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/1957</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Consul General at Irkutsk</hi>
                                    (<persName corresp="#p_HEL1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Harris</hi></persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d285fn1">Senat
                                    via the Legation in China.</note></head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-06-20T15:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">June 20,
                                            1918, 3 p.m.</hi></date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Your May 31 much garbled.<note n="2" xml:id="d285fn2"><hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_182">p.
                                    182</ref>.</note> No plans yet formulated to bring
                                Czecho-Slovaks from Vladivostok.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed><persName corresp="#p_LR1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi></persName></signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>